{
    "id": "287",
    "title": "Indications for Paxlovid",
    "desc": "Indications for Paxlovid Prescribing assists in determining if Paxlovid (ritonovir-boosted nirmatrelvir) is appropriate therapy in a COVID positive adult patient.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/science/science-briefs/underlying-evidence-table.html",
                "text": "Scientific Evidence for Conditions Associated with Higher Risk for Severe COVID-19"
            },
            {
                "href": "https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/hcp/clinical-care/underlyingconditions.html",
                "text": "Underlying Medical Conditions Associated with Higher Risk for Severe COVID-19: Information for Healthcare Professionals"
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.fda.gov/media/155050/download",
                "text": "FDA Factsheet for Healthcare Providers: Emergency Use Authorization for Paxlovid"
            }
        ],
        "evidence": "<p>Inclusion criteria (must fulfill all 5 to evaluate for Paxlovid):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&gt;12 years old and &gt;40 kg.</li>\n<li>Mild to moderate COVID-19 disease as defined by the <a href=\"https://www.covid19treatmentguidelines.nih.gov/overview/clinical-spectrum/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">NIH</a>.</li>\n<li>Symptoms began &le;5 days prior.</li>\n<li>eGFR &gt;30 mL/min.</li>\n<li>Patient does not have severe hepatic impairment (does not have Child-Pugh Class C).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>High risk conditions (having any 1 of the following results is indication for Paxlovid):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ADHD</li>\n<li>Age &gt;50 years</li>\n<li>Alcoholic liver disease</li>\n<li>Asthma</li>\n<li>Autoimmune hepatitis</li>\n<li>Bronchiectasis</li>\n<li>Cancer</li>\n<li>Cardiomyopathy</li>\n<li>Cerebral palsy</li>\n<li>Cerebrovascular disease</li>\n<li>Chronic kidney disease</li>\n<li>Cirrhosis</li>\n<li>Congenital malformations</li>\n<li>COPD</li>\n<li>Coronary artery disease</li>\n<li>Cystic fibrosis</li>\n<li>Dementia</li>\n<li>Diabetes type 1 or 2</li>\n<li>Heart failure</li>\n<li>HIV</li>\n<li>Intellectual and developmental disabilities</li>\n<li>Interstitial lung disease</li>\n<li>Learning disabilities</li>\n<li>Limitations with self care/ADLs</li>\n<li>Mood disorders</li>\n<li>Nonalcoholic fatty liver disease</li>\n<li>Obesity (BMI &gt;30 or &gt;95th %ile in children)</li>\n<li>Physical inactivity</li>\n<li>Pregnancy</li>\n<li>Primary immunodeficiencies</li>\n<li>Pulmonary embolism</li>\n<li>Pulmonary hypertension&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Schizophrenia spectrum disorders</li>\n<li>Sickle cell or thalassemia</li>\n<li>Smoking history or current smoker</li>\n<li>Solid organ or hematopoietic cell transplantation</li>\n<li>Spinal cord injuries</li>\n<li>Stroke or cerebrovascular disease</li>\n<li>Substance use disorder</li>\n<li>Tuberculosis</li>\n<li>Unvaccinated or not up to date with vaccines</li>\n<li>Use of corticosteroids or other immunosuppressive medications</li>\n</ul>",
        "facts": "",
        "estimation": [],
        "primary_complains": [
            "Cough",
